Figgie International Inc. said it bought back 1,972,515 Class A shares, which included 23,552 from odd lot holders, and 278,289 Class B shares tendered in a buy-back offer that expired Sept. 20. 

The company said it bought back one million shares of Class A stock tendered for the indicated offer of $78 a share and the remainder prorated at 50%.
It also bought all Class B shares at $94 a share.
The fire protection, electronics and industrial products concern had 5.4 million shares outstanding prior to the offer. 

